Femi Fani-Kayode, former Aviation Minister, has condemned the assassination of Ahmed Gulak, a former aide to ex-President Goodluck Jonathan. Fani-Kayode maintained that Gulak was killed by skilled professionals who trailed and targeted him. He described them as cowards. In a tweet, Fani-Kayode wrote: “I condemn the assassination of my old friend & former Special Assistant to @GEJonathan, Ahmed Gulak, in Owerri this morning. “The cowards trailed him, targeted him, identified him and killed him. This was the handiwork of skilled professionals. May the soul of Ahmed rest in peace.” Gulak was killed on his way to Sam Mbakwe Airport Owerri in Imo State on Sunday. Following his death, the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) was linked to the assassination, an allegation they have since denied. The Imo State Police Command said that armed bandits were responsible for Gulak’s death Gunmen murder Jonathan’s ex-adviser Ahmed Gulak in Imo 